docs.abstract: Black Friday used to be all about midnight fights, endless lines and major markdowns on televisions. Like the rest of retailing, so much has changed.
docs.snippet: Black Friday used to be all about midnight fights, endless lines and major markdowns on televisions. Like the rest of retailing, so much has changed.
docs.lead_paragraph: Black Friday has long been, and will most likely remain, the busiest shopping day of the year.

headline.main: Fistfights and Long Lines on Black Friday? Not as Much Anymore.
headline.print_headline: Wild Day For Retail Becomes Tamer

docs.abstract: The wedding retailer, the country’s largest, said its more than 300 stores will remain open as it seeks to shed over $400 million in debt.
docs.snippet: The wedding retailer, the country’s largest, said its more than 300 stores will remain open as it seeks to shed over $400 million in debt.
docs.lead_paragraph: David’s Bridal, the largest wedding retailer in the country, filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection on Monday as it tries to shed more than $400 million in debt and adjust to new rivals, but it promised brides that no one would lose their gowns.

headline.main: David’s Bridal Files for Bankruptcy, but Brides Will Get Their Dresses
headline.print_headline: David’s Bridal Files for Bankruptcy Protection

docs.abstract: Malibu has one of the largest concentrations of rehabilitation centers and sober living homes in the United States. Several have had to evacuate clients.

docs.abstract: Less than a year ago, every major economy was expanding at once. Now, the slowdown holds the potential to intensify the sense of grievance roiling many societies.
docs.snippet: Less than a year ago, every major economy was expanding at once. Now, the slowdown holds the potential to intensify the sense of grievance roiling many societies.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Only a few months ago, the world’s fortunes appeared increasingly robust. For the first time since the wealth-destroying agony of the global financial crisis, every major economy was growing in unison.

headline.main: Global Growth Cools, Leaving Scars of ’08 Unhealed
headline.print_headline: As the Global Economy Cools, Millions Are Still Short of a Full Recovery

docs.abstract: “We both naturally despise the Chinese Communist Party,” the fugitive, Guo Wengui said, explaining his partnership with the former Trump strategist Stephen K. Bannon.

docs.abstract: India’s second-largest airline is out of cash and operating just nine planes. The outlook for a rescue is grim.
docs.snippet: India’s second-largest airline is out of cash and operating just nine planes. The outlook for a rescue is grim.
docs.lead_paragraph: MUMBAI, India — Jet Airways, which revolutionized Indian aviation after the government ended the monopoly of state-owned carriers, is now on the brink of shutting down, devastated by management missteps and the feisty low-cost airlines that followed in its footsteps.

headline.main: Jet Airways, a Pioneer in India’s Skies, May Stop Flying
headline.print_headline: Jet Airways, India’s First Independent Carrier, Is All but Grounded

docs.abstract: Electric utilities welcomed Gavin Newsom’s proposals but consumer groups said they would let PG&E off the hook while costing taxpayers billions of dollars.
docs.snippet: Electric utilities welcomed Gavin Newsom’s proposals but consumer groups said they would let PG&E off the hook while costing taxpayers billions of dollars.
docs.lead_paragraph: With another wildfire season looming, Gov. Gavin Newsom of California on Friday urged the state Legislature to help Pacific Gas & Electric and other utilities bear the cost of fires started by their equipment.

headline.main: California Governor Seeks to Protect Utilities From the Cost of Wildfires
headline.print_headline: A Plan to Protect Utilities From the Cost of Wildfires

docs.abstract: Senior executives and board members at CBS knew about allegations of sexual misconduct by Leslie Moonves, the chief executive. No one acted to stop him.
docs.snippet: Senior executives and board members at CBS knew about allegations of sexual misconduct by Leslie Moonves, the chief executive. No one acted to stop him.
docs.lead_paragraph: As a draft report prepared by CBS’s outside lawyers now makes clear, many of the company’s employees, including high-ranking executives and even members of its board, were aware of the former chief executive Leslie Moonves’s alleged sexual misconduct and subsequent efforts to conceal it.

headline.main: ‘Disaster for CBS Shareholders’: Damning Report on Moonves Reveals Total Failure at Top
headline.print_headline: CBS Report On Moonves Cites Failure Of Oversight
